Q1> Using the command git version (or git -version) we can check if git is available in our system or not.
Q2> Using the command git init we can initialize the current directory as a new repository.
Q3> git config global.name ""
    git config global.gmail ""
Q4> Using the command git add . we can add all the files in the working area to the staging area.
Q5> Using the command git rm --cached <filename> we can remove a file from staging area.
Q6> Using the command git commit -m "message" we can commit.
Q7> Using the command git restore we can send our changes to remote repository.
Q8> Git clone is used to copy the entire project on your local repository
    However git pull is used to bring some specific files from remote repository to local repository.
